# Serialization Rules

## CRITICAL: Use Gson Only
- **ALWAYS use Gson** for JSON serialization/deserialization
- **NEVER use kotlinx.serialization** annotations (@Serializable)
- Use injected Gson instance from Koin module, never instantiate Gson() directly

## Correct Patterns
```kotlin
// ✅ Correct - Use Gson
val request = gson.fromJson(call.receiveText(), RequestClass::class.java)

// ✅ Correct - Multipart with Gson
val jsonString = part.value.trim()
val request = gson.fromJson(jsonString, RequestClass::class.java)
```

## Incorrect Patterns
```kotlin
// ❌ Wrong - Using kotlinx.serialization
@Serializable
data class Request(...)

// ❌ Wrong - Direct Gson instantiation
val gson = Gson()
val request = gson.fromJson(...)
```

## Request Models
- Place all request models in [src/main/kotlin/data/requests/](mdc:src/main/kotlin/data/requests/)
- Each request class should be in its own file
- Use data classes with proper validation
- No @Serializable annotations

## Route Functions
- Routes should accept injected Gson parameter: `fun Route.routeName(gson: Gson)`
- Use `gson.fromJson(call.receiveText(), RequestClass::class.java)` for deserialization
- Handle both JSON and multipart requests where applicable